--- Dependencies ---
This directory contains all of your project's node packages.
It can be very large and should always be re-created by running npm install.
This is the most important line in any Node.js .gitignore file.
node_modules/

--- Environment Variables ---
This file contains sensitive information like API keys and database credentials.
It should NEVER be committed to version control.
.env

--- Sensitive Configuration Files ---
Specifically ignore your Firebase service account key file.
Leaking this file gives full administrative access to your Firebase project.
serviceAccountKey.json
--- Log Files ---
Log files can contain sensitive user data and grow very large.
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
*.log

--- Operating System Files ---
These files are generated automatically by your operating system and are not part of the project code.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

--- Build Output ---
If you have a build process (e.g., for a frontend framework or TypeScript),
ignore the output directory.
/dist
/build

--- Optional: Editor and IDE Directories ---
Ignore configuration files from code editors like VS Code.
.vscode/